Courtney CAMPLEJOHN, Appellant, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 7580. Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. Feb. 23, 1935. Edward V. Garcia, Francis L. Poor, and Meinhard H. Myerson, all of Jacksonville, Fla., for appellant. John W. Holland, U. S. Atty., and Wm. A. Paisley, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of Jacksonville, Fla.

Before BRYAN, HUTCHESON, and WALKER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
